or \"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'map')\" for `order.items.map`. The `order` returned by `findById` has items, because `create` stores a copy. But `update` was called at line 56-59 with `{ status: 'confirmed', total: payment.amount }`, and Bug 1 means the update replaces the entire record with just those fields + id + updatedAt. So after `createOrder`, the stored order loses its `items`, `customerId`, etc. When `cancelOrder` calls `findById`, the order returned has no `items` field. So Bug 1 is the root cause.\n\n**Bug 6: `OrderService.refundOrder` (line 99)** — `daysSinceCreation >= REFUND_WINDOW_DAYS` should be `>` (strictly greater than) to allow exactly 30 days. The test \"allows refund on exactly day 30\" expects that refund is allowed on day 30. With `>=`, day 30 throws. Should be `>`.\n\nNow let me fix all bugs."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6401,"cache_read_input_tokens":33318,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6401},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"24deab7f-2265-4665-a495-d06fcf74e69f","uuid":"ee9182ea-687b-4be9-8c1e-5361f353caa9"}
