+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01AWLXPE5MFC335fcHzjkFu1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good progress — down from 12 to 3 failures. The orders tests all pass now. Two remaining issues:\n\n1. **Inventory tests failing** — The `handleOrderCreated` is being called on `CREATED` events from the `beforeEach` of the inventory test. But the handlers registered via `registerHandlers()` are stored in the global `globalHandlers` map. The `EventBus.clear()` is never called between tests, so handlers from previous tests accumulate! Looking at the inventory test's `beforeEach` — it creates a new bus, repo, and service, and calls `registerHandlers()`. But the `globalHandlers` map is module-level, shared across all EventBus instances. So each test adds new handlers, and old handlers from previous tests (which reference stale repos with no stock) still fire. The bug is in `EventBus` — the `clear()` method exists but isn't called in tests. But we can't modify tests... Wait, the real bug is that `EventBus` uses global handlers. Each `new EventBus()` should probably have instance-level handlers, not global ones.\n\n2. **Calculator rounding** — The test expects 130.86 but we get 130.87. Let me trace through the math more carefully.\n\nLet me look at the calculator issue first, then the EventBus issue.\n\nFor the calculator:\n- subtotal = 3 * 29.99 + 49.99 = 89.97 + 49.99 = 139.96\n- discount = 139.96 * 0.15 = 20.994 → rounded to 20.99\n- afterDiscount = 139.96 - 20.99 = 118.97 (rounded)\n- tax = 118.97 * 0.1 = 11.897 → rounded to 11.90\n- total = 118.97 + 11.90 = 130.87\n\nBut the test expects 130.86. The test comment says:\n- discount = 139.96 * 0.15 = 20.994 (no intermediate rounding)\n- after discount = 118.966 (no intermediate rounding)\n- tax = 118.966 * 0.1 = 11.8966\n- total = 130.8626 → rounded to 130.86\n\nSo the bug is that the calculator is doing **intermediate rounding** on discount and afterDiscount. The test expects NO intermediate rounding — only final rounding on the total. Let me fix both bugs."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1212,"cache_read_input_tokens":42251,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1212},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"24deab7f-2265-4665-a495-d06fcf74e69f","uuid":"817202ce-dd8b-4ade-a769-b930271627e5"}
